India Threshold for Inflation Is 4%-6%, RBI’S Mohanty Says

-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-09-28T14:28:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/india-threshold-for-inflation-is-4-6-rbi-s-mohanty-says.html
India ’s threshold level for
inflation is in the range of 4 percent to 6 percent, Deepak
Mohanty,  executive director  at the  Reserve Bank  of India, said
in a speech at the  Harvard Business School  yesterday.  Lowering inflation is key to sustaining growth and will
require co-ordination between monetary and fiscal policies, he
said in the speech posted on the central bank’s website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
